· Nodejs let you run Javascript programs by typing ‘node my_app.js’ in your terminal
· The JS is executed by V8 Javascript Engine
· Node provide a Javascript API to access the network and file system

low response time & high concurrency

use 
  require() 
to include a module, codes in module are defaultly private

use 
  exports. 
to expose any piece of code you want
NPM, node package manager, use 
  npm install module_name 
to install new module

using http module
var http =  require("http");
http.createServer(function(request, response){}).listen(8888)

install mysql module to access mysql database
  npm install mysql@2.0.0-alpha2
everything after @ is the version number


